SIMPLE: chamfer
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chamfer
<hw>Cham"fer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Chamfron</er>.]</ety> <def>The surface formed by cutting away the
arris, or angle, formed by two faces of a piece of timber, stone,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chamfer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Chamfer
<hw>Cham"fer</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Chamfered</conjf> ; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Chamfering</conjf>. <pr>(<?/)</pr>]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Carp.)</fld> <def>To cut a furrow in, as in a
column; to groove; to channel; to flute.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make a chamfer on.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chamfret</ent>⟦br⟧
